The number of systems you can switch on and off, settings you can personalise and buttons you can press are so numerous it's not easy to test them all in a foreign city. We like the way the Q50 looks, and the fact it's a new upstart amongst the established Germans (and Lexus, lest we forget). It's comfortable and economical too, but (yes, there's a but) we're not sure all its systems add to its driving experience. In all likelihood you'll find your favourite one, and stay in it.
